At Kahani plantation a piece of coconut trunk with the exterior decayed contained five L I , three L3 (of which two were prepupae), six pupae and ten adults of 0. insularis.
Some 48 Oryctes L3 were examined, and all were of healthy appearance; four were dissected, but none had any nematodes in the fermentation chamber.
