Development of the ovaries of 0. gigas
Discussions with agricultural extension officers and plantation managers indicate that on the north-west coast of Madagascar the heaviest attack by Oryctes occurs in the rainy season (November to April). This would indicate that the adults of Oryctes were most active during this period.
At Ankivanja, females of 0. gigas were collected and dissected in July, August and September and the results are given in Table VIII.

